To be noted, in making this request this Court has also noticed the pendency in the Salem Commercial Court as reflected in the 'National Judicial Data Grid' ('NJDG');
ii) Salem Commercial Court to decide the Section 9 application de hors this order i.e., untrammelled by this order;
https://www.mhc.tn.gov.in/judis iii) This means that on or before 30.04.2024, Salem Commercial Court would either grant or refuse interim measure sought for under Section 9 of A and C Act;

It is open to the parties to make a prayer to advance the hearing;
v) After Salem Commercial Court decides Arb.O.P.No.1 of 2024 either by granting or refusing the interim measure, it will be open to any party /parties aggrieved to come before this Court by way of appeal/appeals under Section 37(1)(b) of A and C Act.
